MD=1.0, p=0.025, 95% CI 0.1 to 1.9). The anchoring bias intervention reduced 
screening intention (MD=0.8, p=0.044, 95% CI 0.6 to 1.0) and cancer anxiety 
(MD=0.3, p=0.002, 95% CI 0.1 to 0.4) across all conditions.
CONCLUSION: Older adults may reduce their screening intention without reporting 
increased cancer anxiety when clinicians use a more confronting strategy 
communicating they may not live long enough to benefit and add an explicit 
explanation why the recommendation has changed.
TRIAL REGISTRATION NUMBER: Australian New Zealand Clinical Trials Registry 
(ACTRN12618001306202; Results).

