This work begins with the difference between sex and gender, then show that the 
contrasts in the field of health between men and women can be explained: by the 
construction of gender of consultants and health service providers, by the 
structure of the services themselves of health (which also reflects gender 
constructions), and by the reproduction of gender patterns through education and 
research. The work shows the need to include a gender perspective in health 
research.

